**Overall Meaning:**

This verse explains that the flag of the universe, representing the Brahma-loka and everything above, is essentially the foot of Krishna. It further states that the Srivatsa mark, symbolizing prosperity, exists with auspicious signs, implying its divine and powerful nature. 
